SIMPLE: tile
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tile
<hw>Tile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See 2d
<er>Tiler</er>.]</ety> <def>To protect from the intrusion of the
uninitiated; <as>as, to <ex>tile</ex> a Masonic lodge</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tile</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tile
<hw>Tile</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>tile</ets>,
<ets>tigel</ets>, AS. <ets>tigel</ets>, <ets>tigol</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>tegula</ets>, from <ets>tegere</ets> to cover. See <er>Thatch</er>,
and cf. <er>Tegular</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A plate, or thin
piece, of baked clay, used for covering the roofs of buildings, for
floors, for drains, and often for ornamental mantel works.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A small slab of
marble or other material used for flooring.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A
plate of metal used for roofing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Metal.)</fld> <def>A small, flat piece of dried
earth or earthenware, used to cover vessels in which metals are
fused.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A draintile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A stiff hat.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>
<rj><au>Dickens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Tile drain</b></col>, <cd>a drain made of tiles.</cd> --
<col><b>Tile earth</b></col>, <cd>a species of strong, clayey earth;
stiff and stubborn land.</cd> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark> -- <col><b>Tile
kiln</b></col>, <cd>a kiln in which tiles are burnt; a tilery.</cd> --
<col><b>Tile ore</b></col> <fld>(Min.)</fld>, <cd>an earthy variety of
cuprite.</cd> -- <col><b>Tile red</b></col>, <cd>light red like the
color of tiles or bricks.</cd> -- <col><b>Tile tea</b></col>, <cd>a kind
of hard, flat brick tea. See <cref>Brick tea</cref>, under
<er>Brick</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tile</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Tile
<hw>Tile</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Tiled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Tiling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To cover with tiles;
<as>as, to <ex>tile</ex> a house</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: To cover, as if with tiles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The muscle, sinew, and vein,⟦br⟧
Which <qex>tile</qex> this house, will come again.</q>
<rj><qau>Donne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tile-drain</ent>⟦br⟧
